Randall S. Dearth  Chairman, Chief Executive Officer and President, Calgon Carbon CorporationAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 5 Board Members in 5 different organizations across 4 different industries.See Board Relationships53$1,882,917As of Fiscal Year 2016
Background

		Mr. Randall S. Dearth, also known as Randy, has been the Chief Executive Officer and President of Calgon Carbon Corporation since August 1, 2012 and also has been its Chairman since May 1, 2014. Mr. Dearth served as the Chief Executive Officer and President of Lanxess Corporation from July 2004 to July 31, 2012. Mr. Dearth joined Bayer Corporation in 1988 as an Automotive Coatings Chemist and served positions of increasing responsibility including President and Chief ... Executive Officer of Bayer Chemicals Corporation. From 1993 to 1997, He served as a Marketing Manager in Germany, where he was responsible for developing the European and Asian markets for monomeric aliphatic isocyanates, which are used in diverse coatings and elastomeric applications. He serves as the Chairman of the Andy Warhol Museum. He has been a Director at Stepan Company since 2012. He has been a Director of Calgon Carbon Corporation since November 2007. He serves as a Trustee of Carnegie Institute. Mr. Dearth served as a Director of American Chemistry Council Inc. Mr. Dearth holds Bachelor Degree in Chemistry from Hiram College and a Master Degree in Polymer Science and Engineering from Case Western Reserve University in Cleveland.Read Full Background




